%3EMumbai%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Nagpur%20bench%20of%20the%20Bombay%20High%20Court%20today%2C%20March%205%2C%20acquitted%20former%20professor%20of%20Delhi%20University%20G.N.%20Saibaba%20and%20five%20others%20in%20a%20case%20accusing%20them%20of%20Maoist%20links.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20division%20bench%20of%20Justice%20Vinay%20G.%20Joshi%20and%20Justice%20Valimiki%20S.%20Menezes%20today%20acquitted%20Saibaba%2C%20along%20with%20journalist%20Prashant%20Rahi%2C%20Mahesh%20Tikri%2C%20Hem%20Keshwdatta%20Mishra%20and%20Vijay%20Nan%20Tikri%20of%20all%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPandu%20Narote%2C%20the%20sixth%20person%20implicated%20in%20the%20case%2C%20and%20was%20convicted%20earlier%20in%202017%2C%20died%20in%20August%202022%2C%20due%20to%20alleged%20delay%20in%20treatment%20while%20in%20jail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20detailed%20order%20is%20awaited%20and%20the%20story%20will%20be%20updated%20as%20when%20the%20order%20copy%20is%20available.%20The%20court%20had%20concluded%20the%20hearing%20and%20reserved%20its%20verdict%20in%20September%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20second%20time%20in%20two%20years%20that%20the%20Nagpur%20bench%20has%20acquitted%20Saibaba%20and%20others.%20On%20October%2014%2C%202022%2C%20the%20same%20court%2C%20comprising%20of%20Justice%20Rohit%20B.%20Deo%20and%20Anil%20Pansare%20had%20overturned%20the%20Gadchiroli%20session%20court%E2%80%99s%20judgement.%20Barring%20Tikri%2C%20who%20was%20convicted%20to%2010%20years%20rigorous%20punishment%2C%20the%20others%20were%20awarded%20life%20sentences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20discharging%20all%20five%20accused%2C%20Justice%20Deo%20had%20observed%20that%20the%20due%20process%20of%20law%20cannot%20be%20sacrificed%20at%20the%20altar%20of%20%E2%80%9Cperceived%20peril%20to%20national%20security%E2%80%9D.%20The%20bench%20directed%20the%20convicts%20to%20be%20released%20forthwith%20from%20jail%20unless%20they%20are%20accused%20in%20any%20other%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20defence%20lawyers%20appearing%20for%20Saibaba%20and%20others%20had%20challenged%20the%20validity%20of%20the%20sanction%20order%20issued%20to%20prosecute%20under%20the%20stringent%20provisions%20of%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20(UAPA).%20They%20had%20relied%20on%20Section%2041%20(A)%20of%20the%20UAPA%20which%20clearly%20states%20that%2C%20%E2%80%9CNo%20court%20shall%20take%20cognizance%20of%20any%20offence%20without%20the%20previous%20sanction%20of%20the%20Central%20Government%20or%20any%20officer%20authorised%20by%20the%20Central%20Government%20on%20this%20behalf%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20HC%20in%202022%20had%20called%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20valid%20sanction%20order%20as%20%E2%80%9Cbad%20in%20law%20and%20invalid%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdvocate%20Nihalsing%20Rathod%2C%20one%20of%20the%20lawyers%20on%20the%20case%20called%20today%E2%80%99s%20judgment%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbold%20and%20brave%E2%80%9D%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20further%20added%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20verdict%20only%20further%20exposes%20the%20prosecution%E2%80%9D.%20Rathod%20said%20that%20the%20verdict%20is%20a%20tribute%20to%2033-year-old%20Pandu%20Narote%2C%20%E2%80%9Can%20innocent%20man%20who%20died%20in%20jail%20awaiting%20this%20verdict%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrashant%20Rahi%E2%80%99s%20daughter%20Shikha%2C%20a%20young%20film%20professional%20who%20has%20spent%20the%20last%20decade%20fighting%20for%20justice%2C%20was%20overcome%20by%20emotions.%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20speechless%20right%20now.%20I%20just%20want%20to%20see%20him%20walk%20out%20of%20the%20jail%20now%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20the%20HC%E2%80%99s%20order%2C%20the%20Nagpur%20central%20jail%20authorities%20had%20refused%20to%20release%20them%20immediately%20and%20meanwhile%2C%20the%20state%20government%20had%20rushed%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20seeking%20stay%20on%20the%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESolicitor%20general%20Tushar%20Mehta%20had%20argued%20before%20the%20apex%20court%20that%20the%20discharge%20order%20was%20passed%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20the%20requisite%20sanction%20was%20not%20sought%20by%20the%20prosecution%20and%20not%20on%20merit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-gn-saibaba-discharges-suspend-new-abnormal%5C%22%3EStrange%20Case%20of%20G.N.%20Saibaba%20and%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20Another%20New%20Abnormal%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhat%20was%20the%20case%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20March%202017%2C%20a%20sessions%20court%20in%20Maharashtra%E2%80%99s%20Gadchiroli%20district%20convicted%20Saibaba%20and%20others%2C%20including%20a%20journalist%20and%20a%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University%20(JNU)%20student%2C%20for%20alleged%20Maoist%20links%20and%20for%20indulging%20in%20activities%20amounting%20to%20waging%20war%20against%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20was%20registered%20in%20the%20Aheri%20police%20station%20in%20Gadchiroli%20district%20in%20Maharashtra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20prosecution%20had%20claimed%20that%20Saibaba%20was%20the%20secretary%20of%20the%20Revolutionary%20Democratic%20Front%20(RDF)%2C%20an%20alleged%20frontal%20organisation%20of%20the%20banned%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Maoist).%20RDF%20is%20banned%20in%20Odisha%20and%20Andhra%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESaibaba%20was%20named%20as%20the%20prime%20accused%20in%20the%20case.%20Of%20the%20electronic%20devices%20seized%20from%20his%20residence%20in%202013%2C%20the%20state%20had%20claimed%20that%20as%20many%20as%20247%20pages%20were%20found%20to%20be%20%E2%80%9Cincriminating%E2%80%9D.%20The%20police%20had%20further%20claimed%20that%20a%20memory%20card%20seized%20from%20Hem%20Mishra%20contained%20certain%20documents%20that%20%E2%80%9Cestablished%E2%80%9D%20Saibaba%E2%80%99s%20deep%20involvement%20in%20the%20activities%20of%20the%20banned%20terrorist%20organisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lower%20court%E2%80%99s%20conviction%20was%20based%20on%20the%20statements%20of%2022%20witnesses.%20Of%20them%2C%20only%20one%20was%20an%20independent%20witness%3B%20the%20rest%20were%20all%20police%20witnesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20had%20held%20Saibaba%20and%20the%20others%20guilty%20under%20various%20provisions%20of%20the%20stringent%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20(UAPA)%20and%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(IPC).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20Saibaba%2C%20who%20is%2090%25%20disabled%20and%20wheelchair-bound%2C%20had%20to%20endure%20serious%20health%20complications.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20wife%2C%20Vasantha%2C%20had%20made%20multiple%20appeals%20to%20the%20state%20and%20the%20higher%20courts%20seeking%20his%20release%20owing%20to%20his%20deteriorating%20health%20condition.%20In%20one%20of%20her%20desperate%20appeals%2C%20Vasantha%20had%20said%20that%20if%20Saibaba%20was%20not%20released%20immediately%20from%20jail%2C%20he%20might%20die.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20possibility%20of%20death%20in%20Indian%20prisons%20is%20not%20unreal%2C%20given%20that%20Narote%2C%20one%20of%20his%20co-accused%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fpandu-narote-gn-saibab-convict-dies-swine-flu%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fpandu-narote-gn-saibab-convict-dies-swine-flu%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1709706130354000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw0M2_alzK4pWYd1fcyJFATs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edied%20of%20swine%20flu%20in%202022%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20allegedly%20because%20of%20lack%20of%20medical%20care.%20Also%2C%20according%20to%20the%20National%20Crime%20Reports%20Bureau%20(NCRB)%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fprison-custodial-death-medical-care%5C%2