a.%20In%20fact%20he%20prefers%20to%20stay%20away%20from%20saying%20much%20on%20the%20economy%20which%20he%20probably%20realises%20is%20the%20Achilles%E2%80%99%20heel%20of%20the%20NDA%E2%80%99s%2010%20year%20rule.%20It%20is%20very%20difficult%20to%20build%20a%20rosy%20narrative%20on%20the%20economy%20when%20long-term%20data%20or%20even%20experience%20on%20the%20ground%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20support%20it%20.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%20he%20chose%20to%20take%20credit%20for%20the%20unusually%20robust%20GDP%20growth%20of%208.4%25%20in%20the%203rd%20quarter%20of%202023-24.%20This%20was%20quickly%20followed%20by%20commentaries%20from%20establishment%20economists%20that%20the%20economy%20is%20poised%20for%20an%20unprecedented%20take%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20official%20narrative%20is%20plagued%20with%20too%20many%20contradictions%20to%20support%20the%20claims%20of%20a%20big%20take-off.%20The%20primary%20contradiction%20that%20has%20emerged%20like%20the%20proverbial%20elephant%20in%20the%20room%20is%20that%20the%20GDP%20growth%20data%20is%20not%20supported%20by%20private%20consumption%20growth%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20broad%20consensus%20among%20both%20economists%20and%20industry%20representatives%20that%20private%20consumption%20growth%20remains%20very%20tepid%2C%20at%203%20%25%20for%202023-24.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20clear%20mismatch%20between%20GDP%20growth%20and%20private%20consumption.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%202023-24%2C%20GDP%20growth%20is%20officially%20projected%20at%207.6%25%20but%20consumption%20growth%20is%20just%20about%203%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%20known%20economist%20and%20former%20Chief%20Statistician%20of%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EIndia%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Pronab%20Sen%20told%20me%20that%20normally%20consumption%20growth%20numbers%20correlate%20very%20closely%20with%20the%20GDP%20growth%20figure.%20He%20says%20if%20GDP%20growth%20is%20X%20percent%20then%20consumption%20growth%20can%20at%20most%20be%200.5%20to%201%20percentage%20points%20less%20than%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20means%20if%20GDP%20growth%20is%208.4%20%25%20for%20the%203rd%20quarter%20of%202022-24%20then%20consumption%20growth%20should%20be%20at%20least%207.4%20%25.%20But%20official%20data%20shows%20trend%20consumption%20growth%20only%20at%20about%203%25.%20This%20major%20contradiction%20remains%20unexplained.%20Experts%20say%20the%20private%20sector%20will%20not%20start%20investing%20in%20fresh%20capacity%20if%20consumption%20growth%20is%20so%20tepid.%20Industry%20does%20not%20look%20at%20headline%20GDP%20growth%20numbers%20but%20at%20consumption%20demand%20before%20deciding%20on%20fresh%20investments.%20No%20wonder%20large%20Indian%20consumer%20companies%20like%20Hindustan%20Unilever%20and%20Bajaj%20Auto%20have%20been%20expressing%20worries%20about%20the%20lack%20of%20meaningful%20growth%20in%20consumption%20demand.%20Recently%2C%20the%20head%20of%20retail%20company%20Shoppers%20Stop%20told%20CNBC%20that%20sales%20have%20been%20flat%20in%20recent%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Fniti-aayong-national-poverty-indicator%5C%22%3EEverything%20Wrong%20With%20NITI%20Aayog%E2%80%99s%20Claim%20of%2024.8%20Crore%20Emerging%20Out%20of%20Poverty%20in%209%20Years%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEconomists%20have%20tried%20to%20speculate%20why%20the%20consumption%20growth%20rate%20remains%20only%20about%20half%20of%20GDP%20growth.%20Their%20conclusion%20is%20that%20GDP%20growth%20is%20overestimated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20the%20much%20touted%20NSSO%20survey%20on%20private%20consumption%20expenditure%20also%20shows%20a%20very%20discouraging%20growth%20of%203%25%20over%2011%20years.%20During%20this%20period%2C%20GDP%20growth%20has%20been%20roughly%206%25.%20Again%2C%20there%20is%20a%20huge%20gap%20between%20GDP%20growth%20and%20consumption%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEconomists%20like%20Arun%20Kumar%2C%20Arvind%20Subramanian%2C%20Santosh%20Mehrotra%2C%20and%20Ashoka%20Mody%20have%20broadly%20argued%20that%20%3Cspan%3EIndia%3C%2Fspan%3E%E2%80%98s%20GDP%20growth%20or%20national%20income%20growth%20measured%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20output%20data%20does%20not%20square%20with%20the%20consumption%20expenditure%20at%20all.%20They%20feel%20that%20GDP%20is%20clearly%20overestimated.%20Simply%20put%2C%20higher%20income%20growth%20must%20be%20accompanied%20by%20higher%20consumption%20or%20higher%20savings.%20It%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20that%20incomes%20are%20rising%20but%20both%20consumption%20and%20household%20savings%20are%20stagnant.%20This%20math%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPronab%20Sen%20says%20this%20situation%20might%20have%20accentuated%20post-Covid%2C%20when%20we%20saw%20a%20K%20shaped%20recovery%20with%20the%20organised%20sector%20doing%20well%20but%20the%20unorganised%20small%20and%20medium%20industry%20losing%20steam.%20The%20output%20data%20system%20in%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EIndia%3C%2Fspan%3E%20extrapolates%20the%20organised%20data%20for%20the%20vast%20unorganised%20sector%20also.%20Normally%20both%20should%20grow%20together.%20But%20after%20demonetisation%2C%20and%20more%20so%20post-Covid%2C%20there%20might%20be%20a%20big%20divergence%20between%20the%20organised%20and%20unorganised%20sector%20output%20growth.%20The%20K%20shaped%20recovery%20is%20a%20consensus%20view%20even%20among%20equity%20researchers%20in%20Mumbai.%20Only%20the%20government%20is%20in%20denial%20about%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20on%20low%20and%20inadequate%20consumption%20growth%20is%20also%20borne%20out%20by%20official%20data%20on%20wages%20of%20regular%20and%20casual%20workers%20over%202017-18%20to%202022-23%2C%20which%20shows%20a%20decline%20in%20real%20terms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20too%20many%20pointers%20to%20the%20big%20gap%20between%20consumption%20growth%20and%20income%2FGDP%20growth.%20Pronab%20Sen%20says%20the%20consistently%20low%20trend%20growth%20in%20private%20consumption%20growth%20is%20very%20worrying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20thus%20be%20too%20early%20to%20celebrate%20a%20robust%20turnaround%20in%20the%20economy%20even%20if%20Modi%20is%20tempted%20to%20do%20so%20in%20his%20election%20campaign.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20piece%20was%20first%20published%20on%20The%20India%20Cable%20%E2%80%93%20a%20premium%20newsletter%20from%20The%20Wire%20%26amp%3B%20Galileo%20Ideas%20%E2%80%93%20and%20has%20been%20updated%20and%20republished%20here.%20To%20subscribe%20to%20The%20India%20Cable%2C%20click%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Ftheindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709610432000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F05091441%2F2356329954_111b0f36bc_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fsluggish-consumption-data-debunks-pm-modis-high-gdp-growth-claims%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22There%20is%20a%20clear%20mismatch%20between%20GDP%20growth%20and%20private%20consumption.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fsluggish-consumption-data-debunks-pm-modis-high-gdp-growth-claims%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20Colorado%20ski%20town%20can't%20fill%20a%20job%20with%20a%20%24167%2C000%20salary%20because%20potential%20candidates%20can't%20afford%20to%20live%20there%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222124%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Steamboat%20springs%2C%20colorado%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e68f8fce7f1785b2e635f4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221411%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESteamboat%20springs%2C%20colorado%3Cp%3ETHEPALMER%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20Steamboat%20Springs%2C%20Colorado%2C%20even%20high-earners%20are%20being%20priced%20out%2C%20NBC%