crisis-restraint%5C%22%3EIndia%20urged%20all%20parties%20to%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%9Cexercise%20of%20restraint%2C%20avoidance%20of%20unilateral%20actions%20to%20change%20the%20status%20quo%2C%20de-escalation%20of%20tensions%20and%20efforts%20to%20maintain%20peace%20and%20stability%20in%20the%20region%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20controversial%20interview%2C%20the%20minister%20had%20claimed%20that%20Taiwan%20had%20not%20added%20any%20new%20sources%20for%20workers%20for%20last%2020%20years%2C%20with%20legal%20migrants%20coming%20from%20only%20four%20countries%2C%20Indonesia%2C%20the%20Philippines%2C%20Thailand%2C%20and%20Vietnam.%20The%20island%20currently%20hosts%20over%20800%2C000%20foreign%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20a%20rapidly%20aging%20population%2C%20Taiwan%20has%20been%20actively%20looking%20to%20bring%20in%20more%20foreign%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20minister%20claimed%20that%20China%20had%20approached%20Myanmar%2C%20Cambodia%2C%20and%20Bangladesh%20for%20bringing%20workers%2C%20but%20all%20three%20countries%20had%20demurred%20under%20pressure%20from%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETaiwan%2C%20which%20was%20looking%20to%20diversify%20its%20sourcing%20of%20manpower%20from%20just%20four%20countries%2C%20would%20also%20have%20looked%20at%20the%20strategic%20value%20of%20getting%20Indian%20labour%20to%20work%20in%20the%20island.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESana%20Hashmi%2C%20who%20is%20a%20fellow%20at%20the%20Taiwan-Asia%20Exchange%20Foundation%20in%20Taipei%20City%2C%20felt%20that%20the%20comments%20by%20the%20minister%20%E2%80%9Cmay%20have%20stemmed%20from%20anxieties%20over%20opposition%20from%20certain%20sections%20regarding%20the%20pact%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAlso%2C%20lack%20of%20familiarity%20with%20India%20plays%20a%20role%20here.%20It%E2%80%99s%20just%20another%20wake%20up%20call%20for%20Taiwan%20to%20understand%20India%20better%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Indian%20scholar%20told%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fi%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHashmi%20also%20noted%20that%20while%20the%20circumstances%20behind%20the%20comments%20remain%20unclear%2C%20%E2%80%9Cit%E2%80%99s%20evident%20that%20they%20do%20not%20represent%20the%20majority%20view%20and%20do%20not%20align%20with%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20policy%20on%20India%2C%20which%20has%20been%20actively%20working%20to%20strengthen%20ties%20with%20India%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Namrata%20Hasija%2C%20a%20research%20fellow%20at%20the%20Delhi-based%20Centre%20for%20China%20Analysis%20and%20Strategy%20said%20that%20if%20such%20statements%20kept%20coming%2C%20it%20would%20harm%20the%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20(Taiwan)%20should%20sensitise%20their%20ministers%20to%20India%20and%20they%20should%20understand%20that%20both%20countries%20have%20come%20a%20long%20way%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Hasija%2C%20whose%20area%20of%20interest%20is%20India-Taiwan%20relations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20highlighted%20the%20evolution%20from%20India%20and%20Taiwan%20not%20being%20prominently%20featured%20in%20each%20other%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20policy%20agendas%20to%20President%20Tsai%20Ing-wen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Feye-on-china-taiwan-thanks-friends-in-india%2Farticleshow%2F78610960.cms%5C%22%3Eactively%20mentioning%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20her%20speeches%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20issuing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Ftaiwan-train-crash-india-deeply-saddened-by-loss-of-lives-in-accident-mea%2Farticle34230445.ece%5C%22%3Estatements%20on%20a%20train%20accident%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fbjp-mps-praise-taiwan-as-democratic-country-as-president-tsai-ing-wen-begins-new-term%2Farticle31635242.ece%5C%22%3EBJP%20lawmakers%3C%2Fa%3E%20attending%20a%20presidential%20inauguration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%2C%20if%20ministers%2C%20politicians%20and%20bureaucrats%20are%20not%20sensitized%20towards%20India%E2%80%A6%20They%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20India%20and%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20understand%20how%20diverse%20India%20is%2C%20then%20such%20such%20hiccups%20will%20keep%20coming%20in%20and%20there%20will%20be%20a%20negative%20image%20about%20Taiwan%20here.%20Why%20give%20fodder%20to%20people%20who%20are%20trying%20to%20dismantle%20the%20relationship%3F%E2%80%9D%20said%20Hasija%2C%20who%20is%20also%20a%20member%20of%20the%20advisory%20committee%20set%20up%20by%20Taiwan%E2%80%99s%20ministry%20of%20labour%20to%20look%20at%20labour%20issues%20with%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20advisory%20committee%20had%20also%20discussed%20the%20minister%E2%80%99s%20remarks%20at%20their%20online%20meeting%20last%20week%2C%20where%20experts%20had%20pointed%20out%20the%20adverse%20consequences%20of%20her%20words.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20contacted%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20TECC%20in%20Delhi%20had%20issued%20a%20statement%20that%20while%20Taiwan%20would%20decide%20the%20number%20of%20Indian%20workers%2C%20India%20would%20recruit%20and%20provide%20training%20as%20per%20requirements.%20It%20also%20asserted%20that%20Indian%20workers%20will%20not%20be%20differentiated%20%E2%80%9Cbased%20on%20race%2C%20skin%20colour%20or%20ethnicity%20as%20long%20as%20they%20meet%20the%20recruitment%20requirements%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTaiwan%E2%80%99s%20Ministry%20of%20Labour%20has%20recently%20held%20a%20consultation%20meeting%20with%20experts%20and%20scholars%20from%20both%20Taiwan%20and%20India%20regarding%20the%20labor%20mobility%20MOU%20and%20has%20taken%20note%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20concerns%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20TECC%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709570641000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04220759%2FUntitled-design-28.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2F