st%20Lutyens%E2%80%99%C2%A0Delhi%20bungalow%20with%20its%20cream-coloured%20leather%20sofa%2C%20red%20lamps%C2%A0strategically%20placed%20around%20the%20room%20throwing%20a%20warm%20glow%2C%20deep-brown%20smooth%20marble%20tables%2C%20and%20a%20large%20silver%20peacock%20statue%C2%A0studded%20with%20colourful%20stones%20glinting%20at%20our%20subject.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHe%20wanted%20himself%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20the%20master%20strategist%20who%C2%A0could%20gauge%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Ejanata%20ka%20mind%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20due%20to%20his%20direct%20connection%20with%C2%A0the%20hearts%20of%20his%20voters%20as%20opposed%20to%20his%20blundering%20colleagues%C2%A0who%20often%20found%20themselves%20blindsided%20by%20the%20vagaries%20of%20public%C2%A0opinion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EPaswan%20may%20have%20artfully%20given%20the%20comment%20a%20positive%20spin%20but%20it%20was%20not%20entirely%20misplaced.%20At%20the%20time%20of%20the%20interview%2C%20he%20had%20already%20worked%20for%20five%20prime%20ministers%20beginning%20his%20stint%20in%20cabinet%20in%201989%20under%20prime%20minister%20V.P.%20Singh%2C%20a%20socialist.%20He%20was%20then%20serving%20in%20his%20sixth%20cabinet%20under%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20the%20most%20popular%20right-wing%20prime%20minister%20the%20country%20has%20had.%20His%20ideological%20trajectory%20was%20hardly%20linear.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%201969%2C%20when%20Paswan%20won%20his%20first%20assembly%20election%20in%20Bihar%2C%C2%A0he%20was%20a%20socialist%20and%20fiercely%20anti-Congress.%20When%20he%20entered%C2%A0Parliament%20as%20a%20first%20time%20MP%20in%201977%2C%20he%20had%20burnished%20his%20identity%C2%A0as%20a%20Congress-baiter.%20In%20the%20first%20three%20decades%20of%20his%20career%2C%20he%20was%C2%A0equally%20critical%20of%20the%20Jana%20Sangh%20and%20its%20later%20avatar%20the%20Bharatiya%C2%A0Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20barring%20a%20close%20to%20three-year%20engagement%20in%C2%A0between.%20But%20in%20the%20last%20six%20years%20of%20his%20political%20career%2C%20he%20had%C2%A0turned%20into%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20cohort.%20His%20hyperbolic%20statements%20on%20Prime%C2%A0Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20made%20him%20sound%20more%20like%20a%20crony.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOn%20October%208%2C%202020%2C%20at%206%3A05%20pm%2C%20Ram%20Vilas%20Paswan%20passed%20away%20at%20the%20Escorts%20Hospital%20in%20Delhi%2C%20where%20he%20had%20been%20undergoing%20treatment%20for%20nearly%20two%20months%20for%20complications%20arising%20out%20of%20heart%20failure%20and%20kidney%20shutdown.%20He%20was%2074%20years%20old.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20the%20obituary%20published%20in%20the%20next%20day%E2%80%99s%20newspaper%2C%20three%20phrases%20that%20were%20commonly%20used%20to%20describe%20him%20in%20the%20many%20obituaries%20were%20%E2%80%9Cweather%20vane%20of%20Indian%20politics%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cpolitical%20opportunist%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9CDalit%20leader%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20title%20of%20%E2%80%98Dalit%20leader%E2%80%99%20is%20the%20least%20contentious%20of%20the%20three%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0though%20many%20of%20his%20critics%20claim%20that%20he%20was%20merely%20a%20bobblehead%C2%A0Dalit%2C%20strategically%20placed%20at%20the%20cabinet%20table%20to%20tick%20the%20boxes.%20It%20is%C2%A0not%20as%20if%20he%20had%20rich%20pickings%20of%20the%20ministries%20in%20the%20six%20cabinets%C2%A0he%20served%20in.%20Barring%20the%20brief%20period%20between%20June%201996%20to%20March%C2%A01998%20when%20he%20was%20the%20Union%20Railway%20Minister%20in%20Deve%20Gowda%C2%A0and%20later%20the%20I.K.%20Gujaral%20cabinet%2C%20Paswan%20did%20not%20head%20any%20meaty%C2%A0portfolio.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04213427%2F1280px-Politicians_campaing_in_Mumbai_-_Flickr_-_Al_Jazeera_English.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04213427%2F1280px-Politicians_campaing_in_Mumbai_-_Flickr_-_Al_Jazeera_English.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04213427%2F1280px-Politicians_campaing_in_Mumbai_-_Flickr_-_Al_Jazeera_English-300x190.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04213427%2F1280px-Politicians_campaing_in_Mumbai_-_Flickr_-_Al_Jazeera_English-1024x649.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-700114%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22761%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPaswan%20together%20with%20Lalu%20Prasad%20Yadav%20(centre)%20and%20Amar%20Singh%20(left)%20at%20a%20party%20rally%20in%20Mumbai%20during%20the%202009%20general%20elections.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%2FAl%20Jazeera%20English%2FCC%20BY-SA%202.0%20DEED.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EI%20had%20a%20curious%20conversation%20with%20Paswan%20in%20August%202018%2C%20which%20throws%20light%20on%20what%20this%20identity%20meant%20for%20him.%20As%20a%20reporter%20for%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20I%20had%20gone%20to%20meet%20him%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20arrests%20of%20activists%20and%20academicians%20Varavara%20Rao%2C%20Arun%20Ferreira%2C%20Sudha%20Bharadwaj%2C%20Vernon%20Gonsalves%20and%20Gautam%20Navlakha%20by%20the%20Pune%20police%20for%20their%20alleged%20involvement%20in%20Elgar%20Parishad%20(Congress%20for%20Speaking%20Aloud).%20The%20Elgar%20Parishad%20itself%20was%20a%20curtain%20raiser%20of%20sorts%20for%20a%20yearly%20celebration%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98Battle%20of%20Bhima%20Koregaon%E2%80%99.%20In%201818%2C%20it%20was%20during%20this%20battle%20that%20Dalit%20soldiers%20of%20the%20British%20army%2C%20mostly%20Mahars%2C%20trounced%20the%20troops%20of%20the%20local%20ruler%2C%20Peshwa%20Bajirao%20II%2C%20a%20Brahmin.%20Every%20year%20on%20January%201%2C%20Ambedkarite%20Dalits%20gather%20at%20Bhima%20Koregaon%20to%20pay%20their%20respect%20at%20the%20Vijay%20Sthamb%20(Victory%20Pillar).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20year%C2%A02018%20was%20to%20be%20the%20200th%20commemoration%20of%20the%20battle.%20However%2C%C2%A0that%20year%20saw%20violent%20clashes%20between%20Dalit%20and%20Maratha%20groups%C2%A0instead%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20death%20of%20at%20least%20one%20person%20and%20injuries%C2%A0to%20several%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAgainst%20the%20backdrop%20of%20these%20arrests%2C%20the%20phrase%20%E2%80%98Urban%20Naxals%E2%80%99%20was%20introduced%20to%20the%20public%20lexicon%20by%20the%20ruling%20government%2C%20and%20has%20since%20been%20weaponised%20against%20any%20anti-establishment%20person%20who%20may%20or%20may%20not%20be%20inclined%20to%20the%20Left.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAs%20the%20Dalit%20face%20of%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%2C%20I%20had%20hoped%20that%20Paswan%20would%20have%20a%20view.%20He%20did%2C%20except%2C%20he%20did%20not%20want%20it%20to%20be%20printed.%20He%20did%20not%20weigh%20in%20on%20the%20arrests%20but%20instead%C2%A0spoke%20about%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98Urban%20Naxals%E2%80%99.%20He%20cringed%20at%20it%20and%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CA%20bit%20of%20Naxalism%20is%20essential.%20If%20the%20Dalits%20do%20not%20agitate%20they%20will%20not%20get%20their%20rights.%E2%80%9D%20While%20he%20was%20clear%20on%20his%20ideological%20position%2C%20he%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20willing%20to%20voice%20it%20publicly.%20It%20could%20have%20easily%20cost%20him%20his%20cabinet%20berth.%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20more%20inclined%20towards%20Naxalism%20than%20democracy%20when%20I%20began%20my%20political%20life%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20proclaimed%2C%20without%20caring%20to%20explain%20his%20reasons%20for%20saying%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20conversation%20then%20veered%20to%20religion.%20%E2%80%9CI%20never%20grew%20up%20as%20a%20believer%2C%20and%20in%20my%20youth%2C%20I%20was%20an%20avowed%20atheist.%20I%20can%20no%20longer%20proclaim%20myself%20as%20one%20now%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20So%20has%20he%20now%20turned%20into%20a%20believer%3F%20%E2%80%9CNot%20really.%20I%20just%20don%E2%80%99t%20stay%20away%20from%20pujas%20or%20other%20ritualistic%20ceremonies%20that%20happen%20at%20home.%20After%20all%2C%20I%20have%20to%20keep%20my%20family%20in%20good%20humour%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHere%20was%20a%20man%20who%20was%20struggling%20against%20his%20own%20convictions%20and%20beliefs.%20The%20inherent%20contradictions%20between%20personal%20beliefs%20and%20professional%20compulsions%20are%20worth%20telling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAhead%20of%20the%201996%20elections%2C%20Delhi%20corridors%20were%20abuzz%20with%C2%A0predictions%20about%20a%20possible%20sweep%20by%20the%20BJP.%20Many%20armchair%C2%A0analysts%20claimed%20that%20even%20if%20the%20BJP%20did%20not%20get%20the%20magic%20number%2C%C2%A0it%20would%20come%20close%20enough%20to%20rule%20comfortably%20for%20the%20next%20five%C2%A0years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAll%20predictions%20came%20to%20nought.%20BJP%20emerged%20as%20the%20single%C2%A0largest%20party%20with%20161%20seats%20but%20was%20far%20behind%20the%20majority%20mark.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Congress%20was%20a%20close%20runner-up%20with%20140%20seats.%20Social%20scientist%C2%A0Rajani%20Kothari%20described%20the%20results%20thus%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Indian%20electorate%2C%20by%20giving%20what%20the%20media%20calls%C2%A0a%20fractured%20verdict%2C%20desires%20something%20quite%20different%C2%A0from%20what%20has%20been%20provided%20so%20far%20by%20the%20Congress%2C%20the%C2%A0Communist%2C%20and%20the%20two%20combinations%20of%20anti-Congress%20parties%20in%201977%20and%201989%2C%20the%20electorate%20too%20was%20not%20all%20that%C2%A0clear%20or%20united%20in%20its%20thinking%20in%20doing%20this%3B%20in%20large%20parts%20it%C2%A0was%20found%20to%20be%20exercising%20its%20vote%20almost%20in%20a%20fit%20of%20absent-mindedness%2C%20no%20doubt%20still%20turning%20up%20in%20large%20numbers%C2%A0despite%20the%20searing%20heat%20and%20the%20absence%20of%20any%20vigorous%C2%A0campaign%20or%20sense%20of%20excitement%20around%20them%2C%20but%20in%20many%C2%A0ways%20apathetic%20and%20resigned%20to%20whatever%20may%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAt%20161%20seats%2C%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20tally%20was%20still%20impressive%3B%20they%20added%2040%20new%20seats%20to%20their%20tally%20(BJP%20was%20at%20120%20in%201991).%20It%20was%20certainly%20a%20jump%2C%20but%20not%20the%20leap%20that%20they%20needed.%20Half%20of%20the%20country%20remained%20averse%20to%20the%20BJP.%20Barring%20six%20seats%20in%20Karnataka%2C%20the%20party%20could%20not%20win%20any%20seats%20in%20the%20four%20southern%20states%20%E2%80%93%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20Kerala%2C%20Karnataka%20and%20Tamil%20Nadu.%20Significantly%2C%20the%20Congress%20won%20fourteen%20seats%20less%20than%20what%20it%20got%20in%201977%20when%20it%20was%20bruised%20in%20the%20Janata%20wave.%20President%20Shankar%20Dayal%20Sharma%20invited%20A.B.%20Vajpayee%20as%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20single%20largest%20party%20to%20form%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOn%20May%2027%2C%20the%20thirteenth%20day%20after%20Vajpayee%20took%20over%20as%20prime%20minister%2C%20his%20government%20faced%20the%20Parliament%20for%20a%20Motion%20of%20Confidence.%20Perhaps%2C%20well%20aware%20of%20the%20bleak%20outcome%20of%20the%20vote%2C%20Vajpayee%20pugnaciously%20began%20the%20speech%20by%20saying%3A%20The%20biggest%20allegation%20levelled%20against%20us%20is%20that%20we%20are%20a%20communal%20party%20and%20we%20lack%20secular%20credentials.%20Let%20all%20the%20guardians%20of%20the%20so-called%20secularism%20unite%20and%20vote%20the%20BJP%20out%20of%20power.%20Democracy%20is%20a%20game%20of%20numbers%20that%20is%20not%20in%20our%20favour.%20But%20we%20have%20got%20the%20largest%20popular%20mandate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EPaswan%20as%20general%20secretary%20of%20the%20Janata%20Dal%20was%20the%20third%20speaker.%20The%20mandate%2C%20he%20said%2C%20was%20not%20in%20favour%20of%20any%20one%20political%20party%2C%20it%20was%20in%20favour%20of%20a%20coalition%20government%20and%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98secular%20forces%E2%80%99.%20Paswan%20would%20work%20twice%20with%20the%20BJP%20in%20his%20lifetime.%20But%20if%20one%20was%20to%20read%20his%20speech%20from%20the%20Confidence%20Motion%20in%20isolation%2C%20it%20would%20be%20difficult%20to%20imagine%20that%20he%20could%20ever%20evolve%20a%20working%20relationship%20with%20the%20saffron%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20%E2%80%98Ram%20Rath%E2%80%99%20in%20September%201990%20was%20brought%20on%20the%20road%2C%20he%C2%A0stated%2C%20only%20to%20stall%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20Mandal%20Commission%C2%A0report.%20It%20was%20brought%20on%20to%20%E2%80%98usurp%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20poor.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ENext%2C%20he%20came%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98Hindu%20Nation%E2%80%99%20theory%2C%20demolishing%20it%20brick%C2%A0by%20brick.%20In%20all%20the%20states%20currently%20(1996)%2C%20he%20stated%20that%20there%20were%C2%A0only%20Hindu%20chief%20ministers%2C%20be%20it%20Prafulla%20Kumar%20Mahanta%20in%20Assam%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EJ.B.%20Patnaik%20in%20Odisha%2C%20Lalu%20Prasad%20Yadav%20in%20Bihar%20or%20Sahib%20Singh%20Verma%20in%20Delhi%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20Paswan%20asked%2C%20%E2%80%9CTill%20now%20no%20Muslim%20has%20become%20chief%20minister%20of%20any%20state.%20The%20president%2C%20vice%20president%20and%20the%20prime%20minister%20are%20Hindus.%20Hindus%20occupy%20ninety-nine%20per%20cent%20of%20government%20jobs.%20Then%20why%20is%20the%20slogan%20of%20%E2%80%98Hindu%20Nation%E2%80%99%20being%20raised%20again%20and%20again%3F%E2%80%9D*%20Even%20if%20the%20country%2C%20he%20said%2C%20was%20to%20become%20a%20%E2%80%98Hindu%20Nation%E2%80%99%2C%20what%20more%20could%20a%20Hindu%20get%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20core%20essence%20of%20Paswan%E2%80%99s%20argument%20opposing%20the%20%E2%80%98Hindu%C2%A0Nation%E2%80%99%20may%20have%20been%20valid%20but%20it%20was%20factually%20incorrect.%20Until%C2%A0May%201996%2C%20keeping%20Jammu%20%26amp%3B%20Kashmir%20aside%2C%20the%20country%20had%20seven%C2%A0chief%20ministers%20and%20none%20of%20them%20had%20completed%20a%20full%20term.%20A.R.%C2%A0Antulay%20remains%20(till%202023)%20the%20last%20Muslim%20chief%20minister%20that%20the%C2%A0country%20(outside%20of%20J%26amp%3BK)%20saw.%20He%20served%20in%20Maharashtra%20from%20June%C2%A01980%20to%20January%201982%20remaining%20in%20the%20seat%20for%20less%20than%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ECriticising%20the%20BJP%20for%20their%20Opposition%20to%20reservation%20for%20the%20backwards%2C%20Paswan%20then%20asked%2C%20%E2%80%9CAre%20Yadav%2C%20Kurmi%2C%20Kori%2C%20Nai%2C%20Teli%2C%20Tamoli%2C%20Luhar%2C%20Kumhar%2C%20Chaurasia%2C%20Barhai%2C%20Mallah%2C%20Nishad%2C%20Bheel%2C%20Paswan%20and%20Chamar%20(various%20backward%20and%20Dalit%20castes)%20not%20Hindu%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20several%20of%20his%20parliamentary%20speeches%20from%201977%20onwards%2C%20Paswan%20has%20again%20and%20again%2C%20revisited%20the%20question%20of%20the%20origin%20of%20Muslims%20in%20India%20and%20the%20RSS%20propaganda%20on%20Mughals.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20has%20repeatedly%20been%20said%20that%20Muslims%20are%20the%20progeny%20of%20Babar%20who%20came%20here%20in%201526.%20When%20he%20came%20here%2C%20Ibrahim%20Lodhi%20was%20on%20the%20throne.%20Before%20Ibrahim%20Lodhi%2C%20the%20Khilji%20dynasty%20was%20in%20power%20and%20before%20that%20Tughlaq%20dynasty%20was%20ruling%20India.%20Before%20the%20Tughlaq%20Dynasty%2C%20there%20was%20the%20Slave%20Dynasty%20and%20before%20that%20Mohammad%20Ghori%20was%20the%20ruler%20of%20India.%20All%20these%20rulers%20were%20not%20Hindus%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Dalits%2C%20he%20said%2C%20embraced%20Islam%20to%20escape%20the%20humiliations%C2%A0they%20had%20to%20suffer%20daily%20under%20a%20Brahminical%20Hindu%20order.%C2%A0After%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20demolition%2C%20the%20BJP%20had%20become%20a%C2%A0pariah.%20They%20had%20accepted%20the%20offer%20of%20President%20Shankar%20Dayal%C2%A0Sharma%20in%20the%20hope%20that%20they%20would%20be%20able%20to%20gather%20allies%20and%C2%A0tease%20away%20MPs%20from%20smaller%20parties.%20But%20none%20came.%20They%20stood%C2%A0bitterly%20isolated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20debate%20on%20the%20Motion%20of%20Confidence%20continued%20over%20two%C2%A0days.%20On%20the%20second%20day%2C%20Vajpayee%20tendered%20his%20resignation%20on%20the%C2%A0floor%20of%20the%20house%2C%20not%20waiting%20for%20the%20final%20vote%20that%20would%20have%C2%A0revealed%20how%20far%20off%20the%20mark%20the%20party%20was.%20Deve%20Gowda%20had%C2%A0already%20been%20waiting%20in%20the%20wings%20for%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%3Cem%3ESobhana%20K.%20Nair%20is%20a%20Deputy%20Editor%20with%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0The%20Hindu%2C%20%3Cem%3Ecovering%20both%20politics%20and%20policy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709569771000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04213049%2FUntitled-design-27.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-contradictions-between-ram-vilas-pas